# Use `.claude` Guidance First

- Treat `.claude/` as the primary source of project architecture, style, and workflow guidance.
- Before planning or editing code, read the relevant docs under `.claude/documents/`.
- If root-level docs conflict with `.claude` docs, follow `.claude`.
- Keep changes aligned with documented conventions instead of inventing new ones.
